                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>2</p>\n            <p>so ably directed must <sic>eventualy</sic> prostrate that<lb/> great champion of\n                Reform. He is indeed miserably<lb/> humbled already, doubtless there are many\n                Persons<lb/> who would gladly take the Field, but believing the<lb/> holding of him\n                up to contempt is assigning him—<lb/><sic>to</sic> much importance, he is however in\n                proper hands<lb/> and nothing will afford (true believers) so much<lb/>\n                gratification as a continuance of the <hi rend=\"underline\">same</hi> and<lb/> which\n                we have the <sic>assurrance</sic> is to follow “<add>לאיש אשר תורת אמת בפיהו – לרב\n                    המושלים המעוז ומגדל כבוד שמו מהו' יצחק אליעזר נרו</add>”<lb/> !“<add>הפרו\n                    תורתיך</add>”—The <hi rend=\"underline\">D.D</hi> has established his <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">head-quaters</hi><lb/> in the <hi rend=\"underline\">Camp of the\n                    Blind</hi>! Hostilities commenced, on<lb/> the past festivals, when <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">he</hi> boldly attacked, by<lb/> seizing the principles of our\n                Ancient Formulas<lb/> Expelling, <add>כי עת לעשות לי</add>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">Rush</hi>, <add>רות</add> Musaph-Pajutims, <add>פיוטים של\n                    מוסף</add> Ackdumos, &amp; some more<lb/> also he is preparing now a choir,\n                &amp; <del>intend</del>\n                <sic>&amp;</sic> perhaps an<lb/> organ where this will end time alone will\n                develop!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">This mistaken reform, is a novelty, particul<lb/>ary to Persons who\n                have no mind of their own,<lb/> will doubtless for a time be devoured by them<lb/>\n                with avidity—but also vanish like every Phantom as<lb/> soon the <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">Light</hi> (<persName>Dr Wise's</persName> weekly paper in\n                    <add>?</add>) will break on—<lb/> “<add>אקדמות</add>” and as our sages said\n                    “<add>שקר אין לו רגלים</add>”!</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">!<add>שבקי לרוויה ומנפשי נפל</add>”, The new-born <hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">Israelite</hi><lb/> Weekly Pap. By <persName>I.\n                    Weisse</persName> will make its first appearance<lb/> on the <date>1<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">st</hi> of July</date>—its motto is to be “!<add>בן יולד לנו ותהי\n                    מלחמה על שכמו</add>!,” (ignis fatuus)<lb/> and we might say, with Jews. V. 20.\n                    <add>יהי אור</add>! it may <hi rend=\"underline\">probably</hi><lb/> enlighten the\n                    <sic>Gentils</sic> if it does not reform his <sic>Brethern</sic>.<lb/> I will\n                take the liberty of sending you a number when published.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I am Dr Sir, with much esteem, Your mo. ob. Sert</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(7)\"><persName role=\"author\">Dr. I. Mayer</persName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"The following is written sideways in the left margin of the page.\"/>\n            <p>P. S. <add>שמים חשך לאור, ואור לחשך</add>! The <persName>Rev. I. Wise</persName> D.\n                D. the<lb/> Antagonist of the <hi rend=\"underline\">Kabalah</hi>, the Adversirer of\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">Thalmud</hi><lb/> the <sic>Enemie</sic> of the Old obscure\n                Rabbinism, performed<lb/> to day a <hi rend=\"underline\">Kabalistical Function</hi>\n                <add>ואם אין חדש יש חדש</add> He <hi rend=\"underline\">Benshd</hi><lb/> a Child,\n                which died, while he was Benshing it—who is<lb/> the Hypocrite? O\n                    <persName>Moses</persName>! O Tempora!</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
